  "sections": [
    {
      "id": "SEC1",
      "type": "heading",
      "title": "Business Roles in SAP TM"
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "SAP Transportation Management assigns transportation responsibilities through organizational units and business roles. Each role participates in a specific phase of the transportation lifecycle such as planning, execution, monitoring or settlement."
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC3",
      "type": "callout",
      "calloutType": "important",
      "title": "Key Concept",
      "content": "A business role defines WHAT a user performs, while the organizational unit defines WHERE the responsibility belongs."
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC4",
      "type": "heading",
      "title": "Major Business Roles"
    },
